{
  "texts": [
    "The solar plexus can be punched or struck to knock the wind out of someone.",
    "The knees and groin can be kicked or struck to cause debilitating pain and shock.]]]",
    "(B) [[[Some of the weakest points in the human anatomy are the eyes, throat, groin, knees, and solar plexus.",
    "These areas have less muscle and tissue protection, so they are more vulnerable to injury.",
    "Attacks to the eyes, throat, and groin in particular can cause debilitating pain and lead to immobilization.]]]. foot_7"
  ]
}